
# What is Markdown?
Markdown is a lightweight markup language that allows you to format plain text documents using simple and readable syntax

## Why do we use Markdown?
Markdown is used because it provides a simple and human-readable way to format text, making it easy to create well-structured documents without the need for complex HTML

### What symbol will create a heading in Markdown?
you can create headings using the hash symbol (#).

How many do you need to create the largest heading?

To create the largest heading in Markdown, you need one hash symbol (#). This is equivalent to an HTML <h1> element.

How many do you need to create the smallest heading?
To create the smallest heading in Markdown, you need six hash symbols (######). This is equivalent to an HTML

#### When making text bold or italicized for emphasis, it is best practice to use which symbol?
When making text bold, it is best practice to use two asterisks ** or two underscores __

##### How do you create a link with Markdown?
To create a link in Markdown, you can use square brackets [] 

###### What are the three symbols you can use to create an unordered (bulleted) list with Markdown?
You can create an unordered (bulleted) list in Markdown using asterisks *, plus +, or hyphens
